Daemon configuration options: /etc/default/shellinabox

    SHELLINABOX_DATADIR (default: /var/lib/shellinabox)
    SHELLINABOX_USER    (default: shellinabox)
    SHELLINABOX_GROUP   (default: shellinabox)
    SHELLINABOX_PORT    (default: 4200)

SSL/TLS support:

    - requires packages specified in recommends
    - if browser negotiates SNI, daemon will look for matching
      certificate-SERVERNAME.pem in SHELLINABOX_DATADIR, and will
      fallback to certificate.pem

      note: SHELLINABOX_USER/GROUP needs read permission on the
      certificate

root login incorrect:

    - if root login is incorrect (ie. password is not requested), this
      might be due to your securetty configuration.

    - securetty is enabled in /etc/pam.d/login, under the setting
      "auth  requisite  pam_securetty.so", which disallows root logins
      except on tty's listed in /etc/securetty

    - solutions:
        - login as regular user and use su / sudo
        - disable pam_securetty
        - add pts/X to /etc/securetty

